         (summary . "Executes an AutoCAD command")
         (source-kind . "AutoLISP")
         (alphabetic-group . "C")
         (feature-groups . ("Query and Command"))
         (supported-platforms . "Windows and Mac OS")
         (signature . "(command [arguments ...])")
         (arguments . (("arguments" . "Type: Integer, Real, String, or List\nAutoCAD commands and their options.\nThe arguments to the command function can be strings, reals, integers, or points, as expected by the prompt sequence of the executed command. A null string (\"\") is equivalent to pressing Enter on the keyboard. Invoking command with no argument is equivalent to pressing Esc and cancels most AutoCAD commands.")))
         (return-values . "Type: nil\nAlways returns nil.")
         (release-information . nil)
         (history . nil)
         (examples . "The following example sets two variables pt1 and pt2 equal to two point values 1,1 and 1,5. It then uses the command function to issue the AutoCAD LINE command and pass the two point values.\n\n(setq pt1 '(1 1) pt2 '(1 5))\n(1 5)\n\n(command \"._line\" pt1 pt2 \"\")\nnil")
         (url . "https://help.autodesk.com/cloudhelp/2023/ENU/AutoCAD-AutoLISP-Reference/files/GUID-1C989B35-2C5A-47EC-A0C9-71998EDFB157.htm")
         (guid . "GUID-1C989B35-2C5A-47EC-A0C9-71998EDFB157")))
    ("command-s" .
        ((name . "command-s")
         (title . "command-s (AutoLISP)")
         (summary . "Executes an AutoCAD command and the supplied input")
         (source-kind . "AutoLISP")
         (alphabetic-group . "C")
         (feature-groups . ("Query and Command"))
         (supported-platforms . "Windows and Mac OS")
         (signature . "(command-s [cmdname [arguments ...]])")
         (arguments . (("cmdname" . "Type: String\nName of the command to execute.")
                         ("arguments" . "Type: Integer, Real, String, or List\nThe command input to supply to the command being executed.\nThe arguments to the command function can be strings, reals, integers, or points, as expected by the prompt sequence of the executed command. A null string (\"\") is equivalent to pressing Enter on the keyboard.")))
         (return-values . "Type: nil\nnil is returned by the function when the command is done executing on the provided arguments. An *error* is returned when the function fails to complete successfully.")
         (release-information . nil)
         (history . nil)
         (examples . "The following example demonstrates how to execute the AutoCAD CIRCLE command and create a circle with a diameter of 2.75.\n\nCommand: (command-s \"._circle\" \"5,4\" \"_d\" 2.75)\nnil\n\nThe following example demonstrates how to prompt the user for the center point of the circle.\n\nCommand: (setq cPt (getpoint \"\\nSpecify center point: \"))\n(5.0 4.0 0.0)\n\nCommand: (command-s \"._circle\" cPt \"_d\" 2.75)\nnil\n\nThe following is an invalid use of prompting for user input with the command-s function.\n\nCommand: (command-s \"._circle\" (getpoint \"\\nSpecify center point: \") \"_d\" 2.75)")
         (url . "https://help.autodesk.com/cloudhelp/2023/ENU/AutoCAD-AutoLISP-Reference/files/GUID-5C9DC003-3DD2-4770-95E7-7E19A4EE19A1.htm")
         (guid . "GUID-5C9DC003-3DD2-4770-95E7-7E19A4EE19A1")))
    ("cond" .
        ((name . "cond")
         (title . "cond (AutoLISP)")
         (summary . "Serves as the primary conditional function for AutoLISP")
         (source-kind . "AutoLISP")
         (alphabetic-group . "C")
         (feature-groups . ("Equality and Conditional"))
         (supported-platforms . "Windows and Mac OS")
         (signature . "(cond [((test) (result ...)) ...])")
         (arguments . (("test" . "Type: List\nTest condition to be evaluated.")
                         ("result" . "Type: List\nArguments that are executed if the test condition is successful.")))
         (return-values . "Type: T or nil\nThe value of the last expression in the sublist. If there is only one expression in the sublist (that is, if result is missing), the value of the test expression is returned. If no arguments are supplied, cond returns nil.")
         (release-information . nil)
         (history . nil)
         (examples . "The following example uses cond to perform an absolute value calculation:\n\n(cond\n   ((minusp a) (- a))\n   (t a)\n)\n\nIf the variable a is set to the value-10, this returns 10.\n\nAs shown, cond can be used as a case type function. It is common to use T as the last (default) test expression. Here's another simple example. Given a user response string in the variable s, this function tests the response and returns 1 if it is Y or y, 0 if it is N or n; otherwise nil.\n\n(cond\n   ((= s \"Y\") 1)\n   ((= s \"y\") 1)\n   ((= s \"N\") 0)\n   ((= s \"n\") 0)\n   (t nil)\n)")
         (url . "https://help.autodesk.com/cloudhelp/2023/ENU/AutoCAD-AutoLISP-Reference/files/GUID-7BA45202-D95F-4F2D-8D83-965024826074.htm")
         (guid . "GUID-7BA45202-D95F-4F2D-8D83-965024826074")))
    ("cons" .
        ((name . "cons")
