         (history . nil)
         (examples . "Get the name of the first entity in the drawing and assign it to variable e1:\n\n(setq e1 (entnext))\n<Entity name: 2c90520>\n\nDelete the entity named by e1:\n\n(entdel e1)\n<Entity name: 2c90520>\n\nRestore the entity named by e1:\n\n(entdel e1) <Entity name: 2c90520>")
         (url . "https://help.autodesk.com/cloudhelp/2023/ENU/AutoCAD-AutoLISP-Reference/files/GUID-AF320BD5-C83C-4EA0-983E-1EC885F5FC70.htm")
         (guid . "GUID-AF320BD5-C83C-4EA0-983E-1EC885F5FC70")))
    ("entget" .
        ((name . "entget")
         (title . "entget (AutoLISP)")
         (summary . "Retrieves an object's (entity's) definition data")
         (source-kind . "AutoLISP")
         (alphabetic-group . "E")
         (feature-groups . ("Object-Handling"))
         (supported-platforms . "Windows and Mac OS")
         (signature . "(entget ename [applist])")
         (arguments . (("ename" . "Type: Ename (entity name)\nName of the entity being queried. The ename can refer to either a graphical or a nongraphical entity.")
                         ("applist" . "Type: List\nA list of registered application names.")))
         (return-values . "Type: Ename (entity name)\nAn association list containing the entity definition of ename. If you specify the optional applist argument, entget also returns the extended data associated with the specified applications. Objects in the list are assigned AutoCAD DXF™ group codes for each part of the entity data.\nNote that the DXF group codes used by AutoLISP differ slightly from the group codes in a DXF file.")
         (release-information . nil)
         (history . nil)
         (examples . "Assume that the last object created in the drawing is a line drawn from point (1,2) to point (6,5). The following example shows code that retrieves the entity name of the last object with the entlast function, and passes that name to entget:\n\n(entget (entlast))\n((-1 . <Entity name: 1bbd1d0>) (0 . \"LINE\") (330 . <Entity name: 1bbd0c8>)\n(5 . \"6A\") (100 . \"AcDbEntity\") (67 . 0) (410 . \"Model\") (8 . \"0\") (100 . \"AcDbLine\")\n(10 1.0 2.0 0.0) (11 6.0 5.0 0.0) (210 0.0 0.0 1.0))")
         (url . "https://help.autodesk.com/cloudhelp/2023/ENU/AutoCAD-AutoLISP-Reference/files/GUID-12540DAE-C84B-4BDB-AEEC-DDFE5BE3C42A.htm")
         (guid . "GUID-12540DAE-C84B-4BDB-AEEC-DDFE5BE3C42A")))
    ("entlast" .
        ((name . "entlast")
         (title . "entlast (AutoLISP)")
         (summary . "Returns the name of the last nondeleted main object (entity) in the drawing")
         (source-kind . "AutoLISP")
         (alphabetic-group . "E")
         (feature-groups . ("Object-Handling"))
         (supported-platforms . "Windows and Mac OS")
         (signature . "(entlast)")
         (arguments . nil)
         (return-values . "Type: Ename (entity name)\nAn entity name; otherwise nil, if there are no entities in the current drawing.")
         (release-information . nil)
         (history . nil)
         (examples . "Set variable e1 to the name of the last entity added to the drawing:\n\n(setq e1 (entlast))\n<Entity name: 2c90538>\n\nIf your application requires the name of the last nondeleted entity (main entity or subentity), define a function such as the following and call it instead of entlast.\n\n(defun lastent (/ a b)\n  (if (setq a (entlast))         Gets last main entity\n    (while (setq b (entnext a))  If subentities follow, loopsuntil there are no more\n      (setq a b)                 subentities\n    )\n  )\n  a                              Returns last main entity\n)                                or subentity")
         (url . "https://help.autodesk.com/cloudhelp/2023/ENU/AutoCAD-AutoLISP-Reference/files/GUID-75DBA9B2-034B-4377-A4E2-21D37B298D86.htm")
         (guid . "GUID-75DBA9B2-034B-4377-A4E2-21D37B298D86")))
    ("entmake" .
        ((name . "entmake")
         (title . "entmake (AutoLISP)")
         (summary . "Creates a new entity in the drawing")
         (source-kind . "AutoLISP")
         (alphabetic-group . "E")
         (feature-groups . ("Object-Handling"))
         (supported-platforms . "Windows and Mac OS")
         (signature . "(entmake [elist])")
         (arguments . (("elist" . "Type: List (dotted pairs)\nEntity definition data in a format similar to that returned by the entget function. The elist argument must contain all of the information necessary to define the entity. If any required definition data is omitted, entmake returns nil and the entity is rejected. If you omit optional definition data (such as the layer), entmake uses the default value.\nThe entity type (for example, CIRCLE or LINE) must be the first or second field of the elist. If entity type is the second field, it can be preceded only by the entity name. The entmake function ignores the entity name when creating the new entity. If the elist contains an entity handle, entmake ignores that too.")))
         (return-values . "Type: List (dotted pairs)\nIf successful, entmake returns the entity's list of definition data. If entmake is unable to create the entity, it returns nil.\nCompletion of a block definition (entmake of an endblk) returns the block's name rather than the entity data list normally returned.")
         (release-information . nil)
         (history . nil)
         (examples . "The following code creates a green circle (group code 62 is for color, 3 is for green), centered at (4,4) with a radius of 1. The optional layer and linetype fields have been omitted and therefore assume default values.\n\n(entmake '((0 . \"CIRCLE\") (62 . 3) (10 4.0 4.0 0.0) (40 . 1.0)))\n((0 . \"CIRCLE\") (62 . 1) (10 4.0 4.0 0.0) (40 . 1.0))")
         (url . "https://help.autodesk.com/cloudhelp/2023/ENU/AutoCAD-AutoLISP-Reference/files/GUID-D47983BA-1E5D-417D-85B8-6F3DE5F506BA.htm")
         (guid . "GUID-D47983BA-1E5D-417D-85B8-6F3DE5F506BA")))
    ("entmakex" .
        ((name . "entmakex")
         (title . "entmakex (AutoLISP)")
         (summary . "Makes a new object or entity, gives it a handle and entity name (but does not assign an owner), and then returns the new entity name")
         (source-kind . "AutoLISP")
         (alphabetic-group . "E")
         (feature-groups . ("Object-Handling"))
         (supported-platforms . "Windows and Mac OS")
         (signature . "(entmakex [elist])")
         (arguments . (("elist" . "Type: List\nEntity definition data in a format similar to that returned by the entget function. The elist argument must contain all of the information necessary to define the entity. If any required definition data is omitted, entmakex returns nil and the entity is rejected. If you omit optional definition data (such as the layer), entmakex uses the default value.")))
         (return-values . "Type: Ename (entity name)\nIf successful, entmakex returns the name of the entity created. If entmakex is unable to create the entity, the function returns nil.")
         (release-information . nil)
         (history . nil)
         (examples . "(entmakex '((0 . \"CIRCLE\") (62 . 1) (10 4.0 3.0 0.0) (40 . 1.0)))\n<Entity name: 1d45558>")
         (url . "https://help.autodesk.com/cloudhelp/2023/ENU/AutoCAD-AutoLISP-Reference/files/GUID-3F9A2EB2-082D-49DD-8EFD-DAD8F6E9AA6A.htm")
         (guid . "GUID-3F9A2EB2-082D-49DD-8EFD-DAD8F6E9AA6A")))
    ("entmod" .
        ((name . "entmod")
         (title . "entmod (AutoLISP)")
         (summary . "Modifies the definition data of an object (entity)")
         (source-kind . "AutoLISP")
         (alphabetic-group . "E")
         (feature-groups . ("Object-Handling"))
         (supported-platforms . "Windows and Mac OS")
         (signature . "(entmod elist)")
         (arguments . (("elist" . "Type: List\nEntity definition data in a format similar to that returned by the entget function.\nFor entity fields with floating-point values (such as thickness), entmod accepts integer values and converts them to floating point. Similarly, if you supply a floating-point value for an integer entity field (such as color number), entmod truncates it and converts it to an integer.")))
         (return-values . "Type: List or nil\nIf successful, entmod returns the elist supplied to it. If entmod is unable to modify the specified entity, the function returns nil.")
         (release-information . nil)
         (history . nil)
         (examples . "The following sequence of commands obtains the properties of an entity, and then modifies the entity.\n\nSet the en1 variable to the name of the first entity in the drawing:\n\n(setq en1 (entnext))\n<Entity name: 2c90520>\n\nSet a variable named ed to the entity data of entity en1:\n\n(setq ed (entget en1))\n((-1 . <Entity name: 2c90520>) (0 . \"CIRCLE\") (5 . \"4C\") (100 . \"AcDbEntity\") (67 . 0) (8 . \"0\")\n(100 . \"AcDbCircle\") (10 3.45373 6.21635 0.0) (40 . 2.94827) (210 0.0 0.0 1.0))\n\nChanges the layer group in ed from layer 0 to layer 1:\n\n(setq ed (subst (cons 8 \"1\") (assoc 8 ed) ed ))\n((-1 . <Entity name: 2c90520>) (0 . \"CIRCLE\") (5 . \"4C\") (100 . \"AcDbEntity\") (67 . 0) (8 . \"1\")\n(100 . \"AcDbCircle\") (10 3.45373 6.21635 0.0) (40 . 2.94827) (210 0.0 0.0 1.0))\n\nModify the layer of the en1 entity in the drawing:\n\n(entmod ed)((-1 . <Entity name: 2c90520>) (0 . \"CIRCLE\") (5 . \"4C\")\n(100 . \"AcDbEntity\") (67 . 0) (8 . \"1\") (100 . \"AcDbCircle\") (10 3.45373 6.21635 0.0) (40 . 2.94827) (210 0.0 0.0 1.0))")
         (url . "https://help.autodesk.com/cloudhelp/2023/ENU/AutoCAD-AutoLISP-Reference/files/GUID-C7D27797-247E-49B9-937C-0D8C58F4C832.htm")
         (guid . "GUID-C7D27797-247E-49B9-937C-0D8C58F4C832")))
    ("entnext" .
        ((name . "entnext")
         (title . "entnext (AutoLISP)")
         (summary . "Returns the name of the next object (entity) in the drawing")
         (source-kind . "AutoLISP")
         (alphabetic-group . "E")
         (feature-groups . ("Object-Handling"))
         (supported-platforms . "Windows and Mac OS")
         (signature . "(entnext [ename])")
         (arguments . (("ename" . "Type: Ename (entity name)\nThe name of an existing entity.")))
         (return-values . "Type: Ename (entity name) or nil\nIf entnext is called with no arguments, it returns the entity name of the first nondeleted entity in the database. If an ename argument is supplied to entnext, the function returns the entity name of the first nondeleted entity following ename in the database. If there is no next entity in the database, it returns nil. The entnext function returns both main entities and subentities.")
         (release-information . nil)
         (history . nil)
         (examples . "(setq e1 (entnext))    ; Sets e1 to the name of the first entity in  the  drawing\n\n(setq e2 (entnext e1)) ; Sets e2 to the name of the entity following e1")
         (url . "https://help.autodesk.com/cloudhelp/2023/ENU/AutoCAD-AutoLISP-Reference/files/GUID-65924CF5-0C51-4E36-8B38-7A5513951A04.htm")
         (guid . "GUID-65924CF5-0C51-4E36-8B38-7A5513951A04")))
    ("entsel" .
        ((name . "entsel")
         (title . "entsel (AutoLISP)")
         (summary . "Prompts the user to select a single object (entity) by specifying a point")
         (source-kind . "AutoLISP")
         (alphabetic-group . "E")
         (feature-groups . ("User Input"))
         (supported-platforms . "Windows and Mac OS")
         (signature . "(entsel [msg])")
         (arguments . (("msg" . "Type: String\nA prompt string to be displayed to users. If omitted, entsel prompts with the message, \"Select object.\"")))
         (return-values . "Type: List or nil\nA list whose first element is the entity name of the chosen object and whose second element is the coordinates (in terms of the current UCS) of the point used to pick the object.\nThe pick point returned by entsel does not represent a point that lies on the selected object. The point returned is the location of the crosshairs at the time of selection. The relationship between the pick point and the object will vary depending on the size of the pickbox and the current zoom scale.")
         (release-information . nil)
         (history . nil)
         (examples . "The following AutoCAD command sequence illustrates the use of the entsel function and the list returned:\n\nCommand: line\n\nFrom point: 1,1\n\nTo point: 6,6\n\nTo point: Press Enter\n\nCommand: (setq e (entsel \"\\nSelect an object: \"))\n\nSelect an object: 3,3\n\n(<Entity name: 60000014> (3.0 3.0 0.0))")
         (url . "https://help.autodesk.com/cloudhelp/2023/ENU/AutoCAD-AutoLISP-Reference/files/GUID-9D4CF74D-8B8B-4D66-A952-564AFBA254E7.htm")
         (guid . "GUID-9D4CF74D-8B8B-4D66-A952-564AFBA254E7")))
    ("entupd" .
        ((name . "entupd")
         (title . "entupd (AutoLISP)")
         (summary . "Updates the screen image of an object (entity)")
         (source-kind . "AutoLISP")
         (alphabetic-group . "E")
         (feature-groups . ("Object-Handling"))
         (supported-platforms . "Windows and Mac OS")
         (signature . "(entupd ename)")
         (arguments . (("ename" . "Type: Ename (entity name)\nThe name of the entity to be updated on the screen.")))
         (return-values . "Type: Ename (entity name) or nil\nThe updated entity; otherwise nil, if nothing was updated.")
         (release-information . nil)
         (history . nil)
         (examples . "Assuming that the first entity in the drawing is a 3D polyline with several vertices, the following code modifies and redisplays the polyline:\n\n(setq e1 (entnext))       ; Sets e1 to the polyline's entity name\n(setq e2 (entnext e1))    ; Sets e2 to its first vertex\n(setq ed (entget e2))     ; Sets ed to the vertex data\n(setq ed\n  (subst '(10 1.0 2.0)\n    (assoc 10 ed)         ; Changes the vertex's location in ed\n    ed                    ; to point (1,2)\n  )\n)\n(entmod ed)               ; Moves the vertex in the drawing\n(entupd e1)               ; Regenerates the polyline entity e1")
         (url . "https://help.autodesk.com/cloudhelp/2023/ENU/AutoCAD-AutoLISP-Reference/files/GUID-78313F48-676D-49D7-842A-288DD347A783.htm")
         (guid . "GUID-78313F48-676D-49D7-842A-288DD347A783")))
    ("eq" .
        ((name . "eq")
         (title . "eq (AutoLISP)")
         (summary . "Determines whether two expressions are identical")
         (source-kind . "AutoLISP")
         (alphabetic-group . "E")
         (feature-groups . ("Equality and Conditional"))
         (supported-platforms . "Windows and Mac OS")
         (signature . "(eq expr1 expr2)")
         (arguments . (("expr1" . "Type: Integer, Real, String, List, Ename (entity name), T, or nil\nThe expression to be compared.")
                         ("expr2" . "Type: Integer, Real, String, List, Ename (entity name), T, or nil\nThe expression to compare with expr1.")))
         (return-values . "Type: T or nil\nT if the two expressions are identical; otherwise nil.")
         (release-information . nil)
         (history . nil)
         (examples . "Given the following assignments:\n\n(setq f1 '(a b c))\n(setq f2 '(a b c))\n(setq f3 f2)\n\nCompare f1 and f3:\n\n(eq f1 f3)\nnil\n\neq returns nil because f1 and f3, while containing the same value, do not refer to the same list.\n\nCompare f3 and f2:\n\n(eq f3 f2)\nT\n\neq returns T because f3 and f2 refer to the same list.")
         (url . "https://help.autodesk.com/cloudhelp/2023/ENU/AutoCAD-AutoLISP-Reference/files/GUID-BC81B391-48BF-401E-80D0-05A1B578A0FF.htm")
         (guid . "GUID-BC81B391-48BF-401E-80D0-05A1B578A0FF")))
    ("equal" .
        ((name . "equal")
         (title . "equal (AutoLISP)")
         (summary . "Determines whether two expressions are equal")
         (source-kind . "AutoLISP")
         (alphabetic-group . "E")
         (feature-groups . ("Equality and Conditional"))
         (supported-platforms . "Windows and Mac OS")
         (signature . "(equal expr1 expr2 [fuzz])")
         (arguments . (("expr1" . "Type: Integer, Real, String, List, Ename (entity name), T, or nil\nThe expression to be compared.")
                         ("expr2" . "Type: Integer, Real, String, List, Ename (entity name), T, or nil\nThe expression to compare with expr1.")
                         ("fuzz" . "Type: Integer or Real\nA real number defining the maximum amount by which expr1 and expr2 can differ and still be considered equal.")))
         (return-values . "Type: T or nil\nT if the two expressions are equal (evaluate to the same value); otherwise nil.")
         (release-information . nil)
         (history . nil)
         (examples . "Given the following assignments:\n\n(setq f1 '(a b c))\n(setq f2 '(a b c))\n(setq f3 f2)\n(setq a 1.123456)\n(setq b 1.123457)\n\nCompare f1 to f3:\n\n(equal f1 f3)\nT\n\nCompare f3 to f2:\n\n(equal f3 f2)\nT\n\nCompare a to b:\n\n(equal a b)\nnil\n\nThe a and b variables differ by .000001. Compare a to b:, with fuzz argument of .000001:\n\n(equal a b 0.000001)\nT\n\nThe a and b variables differ by an amount equal to the specified fuzz factor, so equal considers the variables equal.")
         (url . "https://help.autodesk.com/cloudhelp/2023/ENU/AutoCAD-AutoLISP-Reference/files/GUID-7E85CB8F-B4DA-42F3-ABD3-89342A11EF9B.htm")
         (guid . "GUID-7E85CB8F-B4DA-42F3-ABD3-89342A11EF9B")))
    ("eval" .
        ((name . "eval")
         (title . "eval (AutoLISP)")
         (summary . "Returns the result of evaluating an AutoLISP expression")
         (source-kind . "AutoLISP")
         (alphabetic-group . "E")
         (feature-groups . ("Function-Handling"))
         (supported-platforms . "Windows and Mac OS")
         (signature . "(eval expr)")
         (arguments . (("expr" . "Type: Integer, Real, String, List, Symbol, Ename (entity name), T, or nil\nThe expression to be evaluated.")))
         (return-values . "Type: Integer, Real, String, List, Symbol, Ename (entity name), T, or nil\nThe result of the expression, after evaluation.")
         (release-information . nil)
         (history . nil)
         (examples . "First, set some variables:\n\n(setq a 123)\n123\n\n(setq b 'a)\nA\n\nNow evaluate some expressions:\n\n(eval 4.0)\n4.0\n\n(eval (abs -10))\n10\n\n(eval a)\n123\n\n(eval b)\n123")
         (url . "https://help.autodesk.com/cloudhelp/2023/ENU/AutoCAD-AutoLISP-Reference/files/GUID-D9B3E6CC-A982-4040-AE6E-6FD63D6C54D0.htm")
         (guid . "GUID-D9B3E6CC-A982-4040-AE6E-6FD63D6C54D0")))
