         (source-kind . "AutoLISP")
         (alphabetic-group . "G")
         (feature-groups . ("User Input"))
         (supported-platforms . "Windows and Mac OS")
         (signature . "(getint [msg])")
         (arguments . (("msg" . "Type: String\nMessage to be displayed to prompt the user; if omitted, no message is displayed.")))
         (return-values . "Type: Integer or nil\nThe integer specified by the user; otherwise nil, if the user presses Enter without entering an integer.")
         (release-information . nil)
         (history . nil)
         (examples . "(setq num (getint))\n15\n15\n\n(setq num (getint \"Enter a number:\"))\nEnter a number: 25\n25\n\n(setq num (getint))\n15.0\nRequires an integer value.\n15\n15")
         (url . "https://help.autodesk.com/cloudhelp/2023/ENU/AutoCAD-AutoLISP-Reference/files/GUID-18D6FF0F-B1DF-447D-BC6C-A46C933EF78B.htm")
         (guid . "GUID-18D6FF0F-B1DF-447D-BC6C-A46C933EF78B")))
    ("getkword" .
        ((name . "getkword")
         (title . "getkword (AutoLISP)")
         (summary . "Pauses for user input of a keyword, and returns that keyword")
         (source-kind . "AutoLISP")
         (alphabetic-group . "G")
         (feature-groups . ("User Input"))
         (supported-platforms . "Windows and Mac OS")
         (signature . "(getkword [msg])")
         (arguments . (("msg" . "Type: String\nMessage to be displayed to prompt the user; if omitted, getkword does not display a prompting message.")))
         (return-values . "Type: String or nil\nA string representing the keyword entered by the user; otherwise nil, if the user presses Enter without typing a keyword. The function also returns nil if it was not preceded by a call to initget to establish one or more keywords.\nIf the user enters a value that is not a valid keyword, getkword displays a warning message and prompts the user to try again.")
         (release-information . nil)
         (history . nil)
         (examples . "The following example shows an initial call to initget that sets up a list of keywords (Yes and No) and disallows null input (bits value equal to 1) to the getkword call that follows:\n\n(initget 1 \"Yes No\")\nnil\n\n(setq x (getkword \"Are you sure? (Yes or No) \"))\nAre you sure? (Yes or No) yes\n\"Yes\"\n\nThe following sequence illustrates what happens if the user enters invalid data in response to getkword:\n\n(initget 1 \"Yes No\")\nnil\n\n(setq x (getkword \"Are you sure? (Yes or No) \"))\nAre you sure? (Yes or No) Maybe\nInvalid option keyword.\nAre you sure? (Yes or No) yes\n\"Yes\"\n\nThe user's response was not one of the keywords defined by the preceding initget, so getkword issued an error message and then prompted the user again with the string supplied in the msg argument.")
         (url . "https://help.autodesk.com/cloudhelp/2023/ENU/AutoCAD-AutoLISP-Reference/files/GUID-9F940144-0D7B-4DA1-BF50-BBF8FB8DFF21.htm")
         (guid . "GUID-9F940144-0D7B-4DA1-BF50-BBF8FB8DFF21")))
    ("getorient" .
        ((name . "getorient")
         (title . "getorient (AutoLISP)")
         (summary . "Pauses for user input of an angle, and returns that angle in radians")
         (source-kind . "AutoLISP")
         (alphabetic-group . "G")
         (feature-groups . ("User Input"))
         (supported-platforms . "Windows and Mac OS")
         (signature . "(getorient [pt] [msg])")
         (arguments . (("pt" . "Type: List\nA 2D base point in the current UCS.\nThe pt argument, if specified, is assumed to be the first of two points, so that the user can show AutoLISP the angle by pointing to one other point. You can supply a 3D base point, but the angle is always measured in the current construction plane.")
                         ("msg" . "Type: String\nMessage to be displayed to prompt the user.")))
         (return-values . "Type: Real or nil\nThe angle specified by the user, in radians, with respect to the current construction plane.")
         (release-information . nil)
         (history . nil)
         (examples . "(setq pt1 (getpoint \"Pick point: \"))\n(4.55028 5.84722 0.0)\n\n(getorient pt1 \"Pick point: \")\n5.61582")
         (url . "https://help.autodesk.com/cloudhelp/2023/ENU/AutoCAD-AutoLISP-Reference/files/GUID-4F8606DD-6453-4D01-84C6-EC8EEBBE2D1A.htm")
         (guid . "GUID-4F8606DD-6453-4D01-84C6-EC8EEBBE2D1A")))
    ("getpoint" .
        ((name . "getpoint")
         (title . "getpoint (AutoLISP)")
         (summary . "Pauses for user input of a point, and returns that point")
         (source-kind . "AutoLISP")
         (alphabetic-group . "G")
         (feature-groups . ("User Input"))
         (supported-platforms . "Windows and Mac OS")
         (signature . "(getpoint [pt] [msg])")
         (arguments . (("pt" . "Type: List\nA 2D or 3D base point in the current UCS.\nNote: getpoint will accept a single integer or real number as the pt argument, and use the AutoCAD direct distance entry mechanism to determine a point. This mechanism uses the value of the AutoCAD LASTPOINT system variable as the starting point, the pt input as the distance, and the current cursor location as the direction from LASTPOINT. The result is a point that is the specified number of units away from LASTPOINT in the direction of the current cursor location.")
                         ("msg" . "Type: String\nMessage to be displayed to prompt the user.")))
         (return-values . "Type: List or nil\nA 3D point, expressed in terms of the current UCS.")
         (release-information . nil)
         (history . nil)
         (examples . "(setq p (getpoint))\n(setq p (getpoint \"Where? \"))\n(setq p (getpoint '(1.5 2.0) \"Second point: \"))")
         (url . "https://help.autodesk.com/cloudhelp/2023/ENU/AutoCAD-AutoLISP-Reference/files/GUID-445F32F0-8A9D-4E1D-976F-DE87CC5267D0.htm")
         (guid . "GUID-445F32F0-8A9D-4E1D-976F-DE87CC5267D0")))
    ("getpropertyvalue" .
        ((name . "getpropertyvalue")
         (title . "getpropertyvalue (AutoLISP)")
         (summary . "Returns the current value of an entity’s property")
         (source-kind . "AutoLISP")
         (alphabetic-group . "G")
         (feature-groups . ("Object-Handling"))
         (supported-platforms . "Windows and Mac OS")
         (signature . "(getpropertyvalue ename propertyname [or collectionName index name])")
         (arguments . (("ename" . "Type: Ename (entity name)\nName of the entity being queried. The ename can refer to either a graphical or a nongraphical entity.")
                         ("propertyname" . "Type: String\nName of the property being queried. For a list of all the valid property names of a given object, use dumpallproperties.")
                         ("collectionName" . "Type: String\nIf the object is a collection object, the Collection name is passed here.")
                         ("index" . "Type: Integer\nThe collection index being queried.")
                         ("name" . "Type: String\nThe name of the property within the collection being queried.")))
         (return-values . "Type: Integer, Real, String, List, T, or nil\nThe value of the entity’s property.")
         (release-information . nil)
         (history . nil)
         (examples . "The following example demonstrates how to get the current radius value of a circle.\n\n(command \"_circle\" \"2,2\" 2)\nnil\n\n(getpropertyvalue (entlast) \"radius\")\n2.0")
         (url . "https://help.autodesk.com/cloudhelp/2023/ENU/AutoCAD-AutoLISP-Reference/files/GUID-8E5913FC-09ED-4C70-AFB7-2431C062E899.htm")
