                         ("mode" . "Type: String\nOne or more valid Object Snap identifiers, such as mid, cen, and so on, separated by commas.")))
         (return-values . "Type: List or nil\nA point; otherwise nil, if the pick did not return an object (for example, if there is no geometry under the pick aperture, or if the geometry is not applicable to the selected object snap mode). The point returned by osnap depends on the current 3D view, the AutoCAD entity around pt, and the setting of the AutoCAD APERTURE system variable.")
