    ("ssadd" .
        ((name . "ssadd")
         (title . "ssadd (AutoLISP)")
         (summary . "Adds an object (entity) to a selection set, or creates a new selection set")
         (source-kind . "AutoLISP")
         (alphabetic-group . "S")
         (feature-groups . ("Selection Set Manipulation"))
         (supported-platforms . "Windows and Mac OS")
         (signature . "(ssadd [ename [ss]])")
         (arguments . (("ename" . "Type: Ename (entity name)\nAn entity name.")
                         ("ss" . "Type: Pickset (selection set)\nA selection set.")))
         (return-values . "Type: Pickset (selection set) or nil\nThe modified selection set passed as the second argument, if successful; otherwise nil.")
         (release-information . nil)
         (history . nil)
         (examples . "When adding an entity to a set, the new entity is added to the existing set, and the set passed as ss is returned as the result. Thus, if the set is assigned to other variables, they also reflect the addition. If the named entity is already in the set, the ssadd operation is ignored and no error is reported.\n\nSet e1 to the name of the first entity in drawing:\n\n(setq e1 (entnext))\n<Entity name: 1d62d60>\n\nSet ss to a null selection set:\n\n(setq ss (ssadd))\n<Selection set: 2>\n\nThe following command adds the e1 entity to the selection set referenced by ss:\n\n(ssadd e1 ss)\n<Selection set: 2>\n\nGet the entity following e1:\n\n(setq e2 (entnext e1))\n<Entity name: 1d62d68>\n\nAdd e2 to the ss entity:\n\n(ssadd e2 ss)\n<Selection set: 2>")
         (url . "https://help.autodesk.com/cloudhelp/2023/ENU/AutoCAD-AutoLISP-Reference/files/GUID-22337977-82F2-4394-B209-39DE2B4B9E86.htm")
         (guid . "GUID-22337977-82F2-4394-B209-39DE2B4B9E86")))
    ("ssdel" .
        ((name . "ssdel")
         (title . "ssdel (AutoLISP)")
         (summary . "Deletes an object (entity) from a selection set")
         (source-kind . "AutoLISP")
         (alphabetic-group . "S")
         (feature-groups . ("Selection Set Manipulation"))
         (supported-platforms . "Windows and Mac OS")
         (signature . "(ssdel ename ss)")
         (arguments . (("ename" . "Type: Ename (entity name)\nAn entity name.")
                         ("ss" . "Type: Pickset (selection set)\nA selection set.")))
         (return-values . "Type: Pickset (selection set) or nil\nThe name of the selection set; otherwise nil, if the specified entity is not in the set.\nNote that the entity is actually deleted from the existing selection set, as opposed to a new set being returned with the element deleted.")
         (release-information . nil)
         (history . nil)
         (examples . "In the following examples, entity name e1 is a member of selection set ss, while entity name e3 is not a member of ss:\n\n(ssdel e1 ss)\n<Selection set: 2>\n\nSelection set ss is returned with entity e1 removed.\n\n(ssdel e3 ss)\nnil\n\nThe function returns nil because e3 is not a member of selection set ss.")
         (url . "https://help.autodesk.com/cloudhelp/2023/ENU/AutoCAD-AutoLISP-Reference/files/GUID-F84DB8CE-B535-453D-977D-AE9D7AD2D7AA.htm")
         (guid . "GUID-F84DB8CE-B535-453D-977D-AE9D7AD2D7AA")))
