    ("vlax-add-cmd" .
        ((name . "vlax-add-cmd")
         (title . "vlax-add-cmd (AutoLISP/ActiveX)")
         (summary . "Adds commands to the AutoCAD built-in command set")
         (source-kind . "AutoLISP/ActiveX")
         (alphabetic-group . "V")
         (feature-groups . ("Application-Handling" "Query and Command"))
         (supported-platforms . "Windows only")
         (signature . "(vlax-add-cmd global-name func-sym [local-name cmd-flags])")
         (arguments . (("global-name" . "Type: String\nThe global name for the command.")
                         ("func-sym" . "Type: Subroutine or Symbol\nA symbol naming an AutoLISP function with zero arguments.")
                         ("local-name" . "Type: String\nA local name for the command (defaults to global-name).")
                         ("cmd-flags" . "Type: Integer\nA numeric value (defaults to ACRX_CMD_MODAL + ACRX_CMD_REDRAW)\nThe primary flags are\nACRX_CMD_MODAL (0) -- Command cannot be invoked while another command is active.\nACRX_CMD_TRANSPARENT (1) -- Command can be invoked while another command is active.\nThe secondary flags are\nACRX_CMD_USEPICKSET (2) -- When the pickfirst set is retrieved it is cleared within AutoCAD. Command will be able to retrieve the pickfirst set. Command cannot retrieve or set grips.\nACRX_CMD_REDRAW (4) -- When the pickfirst set or grip set is retrieved, neither will be cleared within AutoCAD. Command can retrieve the pickfirst set and the grip set.\nIf both ACRX_CMD_USEPICKSET and ACRX_CMD_REDRAW are set, the effect is the same as if just ACRX_CMD_REDRAW is set. For more information about the flags, see the “Command Stack” in the ObjectARX Reference.")))
         (return-values . "Type: String or nil\nThe global-name argument, if successful. The function returns nil if acedRegCmds->addCommand(...) returns an error condition.")
         (release-information . nil)
         (history . nil)
         (examples . "The hello-autocad function in the following example has no c: prefix, but vlax-add-cmd makes it visible as an ObjectARX-style command at the AutoCAD Command prompt:\n\n(defun hello-autocad () (princ \"hello Visual LISP\"))\nHELLO-AUTOCAD\n\n(vlax-add-cmd \"hello-autocad\" 'hello-autocad)\n\"hello-autocad\"")
         (url . "https://help.autodesk.com/cloudhelp/2023/ENU/AutoCAD-AutoLISP-Reference/files/GUID-42392DA4-4A2B-4D34-AA7B-A5ACAF727E54.htm")
         (guid . "GUID-42392DA4-4A2B-4D34-AA7B-A5ACAF727E54")))
