         (source-kind . "AutoLISP/ActiveX")
         (alphabetic-group . "V")
         (feature-groups . ("Property-Handling Functions Reference (AutoLISP/ActiveX)"))
         (supported-platforms . "Windows only")
         (signature . "(vlax-get-property object property)")
         (arguments . (("object" . "Type: VLA-object\nAn object.")
                         ("property" . "Type: Symbol or String\nName of the property to be retrieved.")))
         (return-values . "Type: Integer, Real, String, List, VLA-object, Variant, Safearray, T, or nil\nThe value of the object's property.")
         (release-information . nil)
         (history . nil)
         (examples . "Begin by retrieving a pointer to the root AutoCAD object:\n\n(setq acadObject (vlax-get-acad-object))\n#<VLA-OBJECT IAcadApplication 00a4b2b4>\n\nGet the AutoCAD ActiveDocument property:\n\n(setq acadDocument (vlax-get-property acadObject 'ActiveDocument))\n#<VLA-OBJECT IAcadDocument 00302a18>\n\nThe function returns the current document object.\n\nGet the ModelSpace property of the ActiveDocument object:\n\n(setq mSpace (vlax-get-property acadDocument 'Modelspace))\n#<VLA-OBJECT IAcadModelSpace 00c14b44>\n\nThe model space object of the current document is returned.\n\nConvert a drawing entity to a VLA-object:\n\n(setq vlaobj (vlax-ename->vla-object e))\n#<VLA-OBJECT IAcadLWPolyline 0467114c>\n\nGet the color property of the object:\n\n(vlax-get-property vlaobj 'Color)\n256")
         (url . "https://help.autodesk.com/cloudhelp/2023/ENU/AutoCAD-AutoLISP-Reference/files/GUID-B3F22E35-4666-452F-89C8-5BC15B9E9463.htm")
         (guid . "GUID-B3F22E35-4666-452F-89C8-5BC15B9E9463")))
    ("vlax-import-type-library" .
        ((name . "vlax-import-type-library")
         (title . "vlax-import-type-library (AutoLISP/ActiveX)")
         (summary . "Imports information from a type library")
         (source-kind . "AutoLISP/ActiveX")
         (alphabetic-group . "V")
         (feature-groups . ("Drawing Object Functions Reference (AutoLISP/ActiveX)"))
         (supported-platforms . "Windows only")
         (signature . "(vlax-import-type-library :tlb-filename filename [:methods-prefix mprefix  :properties-prefix pprefix :constants-prefix cprefix])")
         (arguments . (("filename" . "Type: String\nName of the type library. A file can be one of the following types:\n- A type library (TLB) or object library (OLB) file\n- An executable (EXE) file\n- A library (DLL) file containing a type library resource\n- A compound document holding a type library\n- Any other file format that can be understood by the LoadTypeLib API\nIf you omit the path from tlb-filename, AutoCAD looks for the file in the support file search path.")
                         ("mprefix" . "Type: String\nPrefix to be used for method wrapper functions. For example, if the type library contains a Calculate method and the mprefix parameter is set to “cc-”, Visual LISP generates a wrapper function named cc-Calculate. This parameter defaults to “”.")
                         ("pprefix" . "Type: String\nPrefix to be used for property wrapper functions. For example, if the type library contains a Width property with both read and write permissions, and pprefix is set to “cc-”, then Visual LISP generates wrapper functions named cc-get-Width and cc-put-Width. This parameter defaults to “”.")
                         ("cprefix" . "Type: String\nPrefix to be used for constants contained in the type library. For example, if the type library contains a ccMaxCountOfRecords property with both read and write permissions, and cprefix is set to “cc-”, Visual LISP generates a constant named cc-ccMaxCountOfRecords. This parameter defaults to “”.")))
         (return-values . "Type: T or nil\nT, if successful; otherwise, nil if the library could not be imported.")
         (release-information . nil)
         (history . nil)
         (examples . "Import a Microsoft Word type library, assigning the prefix “msw-” to methods and properties, and “mswc-” to constants:\n\n(vlax-import-type-library\n  :tlb-filename \"C:/Program Files (x86)/Microsoft Office/root/Office16/msword.olb\"\n  :methods-prefix \"msw-\"\n  :properties-prefix \"msw-\"\n  :constants-prefix \"mswc-\")\nT")
         (url . "https://help.autodesk.com/cloudhelp/2023/ENU/AutoCAD-AutoLISP-Reference/files/GUID-1699B6A0-C4A6-4BC4-82DF-5040CFF3394A.htm")
         (guid . "GUID-1699B6A0-C4A6-4BC4-82DF-5040CFF3394A")))
    ("vlax-invoke-method" .
        ((name . "vlax-invoke-method")
         (title . "vlax-invoke-method (AutoLISP/ActiveX)")
         (summary . "Calls the specified ActiveX method")
         (source-kind . "AutoLISP/ActiveX")
         (alphabetic-group . "V")
         (feature-groups . ("Method Invocation Functions Reference (AutoLISP/ActiveX)"))
         (supported-platforms . "Windows only")
         (signature . "(vlax-invoke-method obj method arg [arg ...])")
         (arguments . (("obj" . "Type: VLA-object\nAn object.")
                         ("method" . "Type: Symbol or String\nA symbol or string naming the method to be called.")
                         ("arg" . "Type: Integer, Real, String, List, VLA-object, Variant, Safearray, T, or nil\nArgument to be passed to the method called. No argument type checking is performed.")))
         (return-values . "Type: Integer, Real, String, List, VLA-object, Variant, Safearray, T, or nil\nDepends on the method invoked.")
         (release-information . nil)
         (history . nil)
         (examples . "The following example uses the AddCircle method to draw a circle in the current AutoCAD drawing.\n\nThe first argument to AddCircle specifies the location of the center of the circle. The method requires the center to be specified as a variant containing a three-element array of doubles. You can use vlax-3d-point to convert an AutoLISP point list to the required variant data type:\n\n(setq circCenter (vlax-3d-point '(3.0 3.0 0.0)))\n#<variant 8197 ...>\n\nNow use vlax-invoke-method to draw a circle with the AddCircle method:\n\n(setq mycircle (vlax-invoke-method mspace 'AddCircle circCenter 3.0))\n#<VLA-OBJECT IAcadCircle 00bfd6e4>")
         (url . "https://help.autodesk.com/cloudhelp/2023/ENU/AutoCAD-AutoLISP-Reference/files/GUID-A8B097A2-CE86-4B38-B2A9-D6F53EACA8ED.htm")
         (guid . "GUID-A8B097A2-CE86-4B38-B2A9-D6F53EACA8ED")))
    ("vlax-ldata-delete" .
        ((name . "vlax-ldata-delete")
         (title . "vlax-ldata-delete (AutoLISP/ActiveX)")
         (summary . "Erases LISP data from a drawing dictionary")
         (source-kind . "AutoLISP/ActiveX")
         (alphabetic-group . "V")
         (feature-groups . ("Dictionary Functions Reference (AutoLISP/ActiveX)" "Symbol Table and Dictionary-Handling"))
         (supported-platforms . "Windows only")
         (signature . "(vlax-ldata-delete dict key [private])")
         (arguments . (("dict" . "Type: VLA-object or String\nAn object, AutoCAD drawing entity object, or a string naming a global dictionary.")
                         ("key" . "Type: String\nDictionary key.")
                         ("private" . "Type: T or nil\nIf a non-nil value is specified for private and vlax-ldata-delete is called from a separate-namespace VLX, vlax-ldata-delete deletes private LISP data from dict.")))
         (return-values . "Type: T or nil\nT, if successful; otherwise nil (for example, the data did not exist).")
         (release-information . nil)
         (history . nil)
         (examples . "Add LISP data to a dictionary:\n\n(vlax-ldata-put \"dict\" \"key\" '(1))\n(1)\n\nUse vlax-ldata-delete to delete the LISP data:\n\n(vlax-ldata-delete \"dict\" \"key\")\nT\n\nIf vlax-ldata-delete is called again to remove the same data, it returns nil because the data does not exist in the dictionary:\n\n(vlax-ldata-delete \"dict\" \"key\")\nnil")
         (url . "https://help.autodesk.com/cloudhelp/2023/ENU/AutoCAD-AutoLISP-Reference/files/GUID-06F6C8B7-A55C-42DE-BD51-A9FAB68260D3.htm")
